<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Nitrate Measurement in Water</title>
    <style>
        :root {
            --primary: #2F4F4F;
            --primary-light: #3a5f5f;
            --secondary: #778899;
            --accent: #20B2AA;
            --light-bg: #f5f5f5;
            --dark-text: #2d3748;
            --border-color: #e0e0e0;
            --white: #ffffff;
        }

        body {
            font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background-color: var(--light-bg);
            color: var(--dark-text);
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        .container {
            max-width: 900px;
            margin: 30px auto;
            padding: 30px;
            background: var(--white);
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0px 4px 15px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }

        h1 {
            color: var(--primary);
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 25px;
            font-size: 2.2rem;
            border-bottom: 2px solid var(--accent);
            padding-bottom: 10px;
        }

        p {
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            font-size: 1.1rem;
        }

        .info-section {
            margin-top: 30px;
            padding: 20px;
            background: #e3f2fd;
            border-left: 4px solid var(--primary);
            border-radius: 0 5px 5px 0;
            transition: all 0.3s ease;
        }

        .info-section p:last-child {
            margin-bottom: 0;
        }

        .btn {
            display: block;
            margin: 25px auto;
            padding: 12px 25px;
            background-color: var(--primary);
            color: white;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
            font-size: 1rem;
            font-weight: bold;
            transition: all 0.3s ease;
            box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
        }

        .btn:hover {
            background-color: var(--primary-light);
            transform: translateY(-2px);
            box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);
        }

        /* Back button */
        .back-button-container {
            position: fixed;
            top: 20px;
            left: 20px;
            z-index: 1000;
        }

        .back-button {
            background-color: var(--primary);
            color: white;
            border: none;
            padding: 10px 15px;
            font-size: 16px;
            cursor: pointer;
            border-radius: 5px;
            transition: all 0.3s ease;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 5px;
        }

        .back-button:hover {
            background-color: var(--primary-light);
            transform: translateX(-3px);
        }

        /* Highlight important terms */
        .highlight {
            font-weight: bold;
            color: var(--primary);
        }

        .chemical {
            font-weight: bold;
            color: var(--accent);
            font-style: italic;
        }

        .feature-list {
            margin: 20px 0;
            padding-left: 20px;
        }

        .feature-list li {
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        .definition-box {
            background-color: #e1f5fe;
            border-left: 4px solid var(--accent);
            padding: 15px;
            margin: 20px 0;
            border-radius: 0 5px 5px 0;
        }

        .definition-title {
            font-weight: bold;
            color: var(--primary);
            margin-bottom: 8px;
        }

        .sensor-image {
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 500px;
            margin: 20px auto;
            display: block;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
            border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
        }

        .warning-box {
            background-color: #fff3cd;
            border-left: 4px solid #ffc107;
            padding: 15px;
            margin: 20px 0;
            border-radius: 0 5px 5px 0;
        }

        .warning-title {
            font-weight: bold;
            color: #856404;
            margin-bottom: 8px;
        }

        /* Responsive design */
        @media (max-width: 768px) {
            .container {
                margin: 15px;
                padding: 20px;
            }
            
            h1 {
                font-size: 1.8rem;
            }
            
            .back-button-container {
                position: relative;
                top: auto;
                left: auto;
                margin-bottom: 15px;
            }
            
            .back-button {
                position: relative;
                margin: 0 auto 20px;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <!-- Back to Home Button -->
    <div class="back-button-container">
        <button class="back-button" onclick="goBackHome()">&#8592; Back to Parameters</button>
    </div>

    <div class="container">
        <h1>Nitrate (NO₃⁻) in Water Systems</h1>
        
        <div class="definition-box">
            <div class="definition-title">Nitrate (NO₃⁻)</div>
            <p>A water-soluble ion composed of one nitrogen atom and three oxygen atoms, serving as a primary nitrogen source for plants and a key indicator of water quality and pollution.</p>
        </div>

        <p>Nitrate monitoring is essential for protecting aquatic ecosystems, ensuring drinking water safety, and managing agricultural nutrient runoff.</p>

        <button class="btn" onclick="toggleInfo()">Show Measurement Details</button>
        
        <div class="info-section" id="moreInfo" style="display: none;">
            <h2>Primary Sources of Nitrate</h2>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li><span class="highlight">Agricultural runoff:</span> Fertilizers like <span class="chemical">NH₄NO₃</span> (ammonium nitrate) and <span class="chemical">KNO₃</span> (potassium nitrate)</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Wastewater discharge:</span> Treated sewage and septic system effluent</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Animal operations:</span> Manure from concentrated animal feeding operations</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Industrial processes:</span> Food processing, explosives manufacturing, and metal finishing</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Natural sources:</span> Microbial nitrification of ammonia in soils and water</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Atmospheric deposition:</span> Nitrogen oxides from combustion processes</li>
            </ul>

            <img src="images/nitrate-sensor.jpg" alt="Nitrate measurement sensor" class="sensor-image">

            <div class="warning-box">
                <div class="warning-title">Health and Environmental Concerns</div>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="highlight">Methemoglobinemia:</span> "Blue baby syndrome" in infants exposed to high nitrate levels</li>
                    <li><span class="highlight">Eutrophication:</span> Excessive nitrate leads to algal blooms and dead zones</li>
                    <li><span class="highlight">Drinking water standards:</span> EPA maximum contaminant level of 10 mg/L NO₃-N</li>
                    <li><span class="highlight">Aquatic life impacts:</span> Alters ecosystem balance and species composition</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h2>Measurement Techniques</h2>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li><span class="highlight">Ion-selective electrodes:</span> Direct measurement of nitrate ions in water</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Colorimetric methods:</span> Cadmium reduction or chromotropic acid methods</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">UV spectrophotometry:</span> Measures absorbance at 220 nm (with correction at 275 nm)</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Chromatographic methods:</span> Ion chromatography for precise speciation</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Continuous monitoring:</span> In-situ sensors for real-time nitrate tracking</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Nitrogen Cycle Context</h2>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li>Nitrate is the most oxidized form of nitrogen in the nitrogen cycle</li>
                <li>Produced through nitrification (microbial oxidation of ammonia)</li>
                <li>Reduced through denitrification (conversion to N₂ gas)</li>
                <li>Assimilated by plants and algae as a primary nitrogen source</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Management Strategies</h2>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li><span class="highlight">Agricultural best practices:</span> Controlled fertilizer application, cover crops</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Riparian buffers:</span> Vegetated zones along water bodies to filter runoff</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Wetland restoration:</span> Natural nitrate removal through denitrification</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Advanced wastewater treatment:</span> Biological nitrogen removal processes</li>
                <li><span class="highlight">Monitoring programs:</span> Regular water quality assessments</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script>
        function goBackHome() {
            window.location.href = 'parameters';
        }

        function toggleInfo() {
            const info = document.getElementById("moreInfo");
            const button = document.querySelector(".btn");
            
            if (info.style.display === "none") {
                info.style.display = "block";
                button.textContent = "Hide Measurement Details";
            } else {
                info.style.display = "none";
                button.textContent = "Show Measurement Details";
            }
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>